.TH SHUTDOWN 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
shutdown \- power off the system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shutdown
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shutdown
is a thin convenience wrapper around
.BR "sudo systemctl poweroff" .
It takes no arguments and prompts for a sudo password if the user's
cached sudo credentials have expired.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Power off the system:
.B shutdown
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
Reflects the exit status of
.BR "sudo systemctl poweroff" .
On success the system powers off and this command does not return.
.SH AUTHOR
Steve de Bode \- W0FFS
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR reboot (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
